WAIKIKI ( PIX11 ) - A professional surfer is being investigated for attempted murder after she allegedly tried to run over a 73 - year - old woman with her car in Hawaii .
Jill Hansen was arrested May 14 after a brutal attack that may have been sparked by road rage , according to Hawaii News Now .
Police told local outlets that the 30 - year - old surfer followed the 73 - year - old woman through a condo complex 's security gate .
When the victim exited her car , Hansen allegedly rammed her car into her , backed up and tried to hit her again .
